- Dependency
  npm install -D parcel

- Component 
  it is the normal js function it return some piece of "JSX" it is very similar to HTML but it is not the real HTML.
  like : <div class="xyz">
            
         </div> 

  JSX : <div className="xyz">
            
         </div> 




const Header=()=>{
    
   const [loginButton,setloginButton]=useState('Login') 

    
    
    
    return(

        <button onClick={()=>{
            if(loginButton==="Login"){
                setloginButton("Logout");
            }
            else{
                setloginButton("Login");
            }
        }}>


        </button>

    )
}